metadata.name: Night Shift
metadata.description:
COLD CALLING is an ode to life in solitude at the world's northernmost settlement in Svalbard, Norway during the polar night season. 

The collection explores the surrounding elements and captivating ambiance of the Arctic community just south of the North Pole on an island that thousands of polar bears call home.

The photographs in the collection are a part of an ongoing body of work about Svalbard's landscape.

78°13'05.0"N 15°39'19.6"E
